<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!--Transformation version 1.3--><legislativeDoc xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="http://www.lexisnexis.com/xmlschemas/content/public/legislativedoc/1/" schemaVersion="1.0"><legislativeDocHead><citations><citeForThisResource citeDefinition="#7159#349#000064#     2#          416#">Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-416</citeForThisResource></citations><legislativeBodyInfo><jurisdiction><jurisSystem normalizedLongName="Virginia" normalizedShortName="VA"/></jurisdiction></legislativeBodyInfo></legislativeDocHead><legislativeDocBody><statute><level levelType="section"><anchor id="_64.2-416"/><heading><desig>§ 64.2-416.</desig><title>Devises and bequests that fail; how to pass</title></heading><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a"/><heading><desig>A.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Unless a contrary intention appears in the will, and except as provided in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-418"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-418">§ 64.2-418<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#          418#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>:</p></bodyText><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_1"/><heading><desig>1.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If a devise or bequest other than a residuary devise or bequest fails for any reason, it shall become a part of the residue; and</p></bodyText></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_a_2"/><heading><desig>2.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> If the residue is devised or bequeathed to two or more persons and the share of one fails for any reason, such share shall pass to the other residuary devisees or legatees in proportion to their interests in the residue.</p></bodyText></level></level><level levelType="paragraph"><anchor id="_b"/><heading><desig>B.</desig></heading><bodyText><p> Notwithstanding the provisions of <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-2604"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-2604">§§ 64.2-2604<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         2604#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 64.2-2605"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 64.2-2605">64.2-2605<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000064#     2#         2605#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and unless a contrary intention appears in the will, if a testator makes a bequest, not exceeding the value of $ 100, to a legatee and such legatee refuses to take possession of such bequest, then the bequest shall fail and becomes a part of the residue of the testator's estate.</p></bodyText></level><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>1985, c. 592, § 64.1-65.1; <citation normalizedCite="2003 VA CH 253"><content><span normalizedCite="2003 Va. Ch. 253">2003, c. 253<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2003#000253#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2012 VA CH 614"><content><span normalizedCite="2012 Va. Ch. 614">2012, c. 614<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2012#000614#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2014 VA CH 532"><content><span normalizedCite="2014 Va. Ch. 532">2014, c. 532<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2014#000532#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>.</p></bodyText></historyItem></historyGroup></history></level></statute></legislativeDocBody><metadata><dc:metadata xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><dc:identifier identifierScheme="PGUID">urn:contentItem:5K0Y-PVX0-004G-K0BB-00000-00</dc:identifier><dc:source sourceScheme="p